mention.text: the chairman of The agency legislature
His victory in the first popular balloting for Russian president

the Soviet Union By winning up to 57 percent of the vote , Yeltsin avoided a run-off and strengthened The 61-year-old Yeltsin hand against Communist Party stalwarts who oppose The 61-year-old Yeltsin program to transfer ownership of state-owned farms and factories to individuals
Gorbachev , who has never faced a popular election
Moscow Mayor Gavriil Popov and Leningrad Mayor Anatoly Sobchak
former Soviet Prime Minister Nikolai Ryzhkov
a celebration of the Russian Federation 's sovereignty For the first time in its 1,000-year history , the Russian people are electing the Russian people president in a direct vote
former Soviet Interior Minister Vadim Bakatin

former Soviet Interior Minister Vadim Bakatin , who also enjoys Communist support ; Gen. Albert Makashov , a hard-line law-and-order Communist ; Vladimir Zhirinovsky , head of the tiny Liberal Democratic Party ; and Aman Tuleyev , a Siberian active in the trade union movement

Boris Yeltsin elected president ; Born : Feb. 1 , 1931 , in Butka , Siberia , in Russian republic ; 1955 : Construction worker in Sverdlovsk ; 1976 : First secretary , Sverdlovsk District Central Committee ; 1987 : Outburst against conservative archrival Yegor Ligachev
